        title: 'Cookie-Cutter Workouts',
        description:
          'Pre-made splits ignore your recovery signals, injury history, and real-world goals. They grind you down instead of building you up.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Gym-Only Strength',
        description:
          'Isolation machines and body-part splits ignore carries, crawls, and mobility. You get bigger in mirrors but stay fragile in real life.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Static Progressions',
        description:
          'Linear loading schemes repeat the same stress until your body adapts, gains stall, and joints ache. No feedback loop means no forward momentum.',
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: '~/assets/images/failed.png',
      alt: 'Why Most Training Plans Fail',
    }}
  >
